# .gh-token — YOUR personal GitHub token. NEVER commit this (it's gitignored).
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.gh-token` (here, or once at your Projects/ root to cover
#    every migration repo via the walk-up — grove, kernel, greenhouse,
#    skill-kernel-tokens, skill-kernel-components).
# 2. Replace the line below with YOUR OWN token (no quotes, no extra whitespace).
# 3. Run `bash setup-auth.sh` once in each clone. Then plain git push/pull works.
#
# Recommended token: a FINE-GRAINED PAT (github.com -> Settings -> Developer
# settings -> Fine-grained tokens) scoped to ONLY these 5 repositories, with
# Repository permission "Contents: Read and write". Least privilege: it cannot
# create repos or touch anything else. (Creating new repos — rare — needs a
# separate classic admin token, used only for that.)
#
# Your colleague must first be added as a collaborator on the repos (the owner
# runs add-collaborator.sh). Each of you uses YOUR OWN token — never share one.

github_pat_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_OWN_FINE_GRAINED_TOKEN
